WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.890 --> 00:00:03.444
Prof: Okay,
we've already talked about the

00:00:03.444 --> 00:00:05.840
problems of using these texts
historically.

00:00:05.840 --> 00:00:09.206
If you remember,
early in the semester we talked

00:00:09.206 --> 00:00:12.887
about Galatians 1 and 2,
and Acts, and we tried to

00:00:12.887 --> 00:00:17.500
compare exactly when did Paul go
where with regard to Jerusalem,

00:00:17.500 --> 00:00:19.020
Damascus, Antioch.
 

00:00:19.020 --> 00:00:22.808
And we saw that it's very,
very difficult to harmonize

00:00:22.808 --> 00:00:26.454
Galatians 1 and 2 with the
account of Acts in Paul's

00:00:26.454 --> 00:00:28.670
movements around Jerusalem.
 

00:00:28.670 --> 00:00:32.194
We've also got a lot of other
situations where this would be

00:00:32.194 --> 00:00:33.210
very difficult.
 

00:00:33.210 --> 00:00:36.310
I mentioned the differences
between Matthew and Luke as far

00:00:36.310 --> 00:00:37.700
as the birth narratives.
 

00:00:37.700 --> 00:00:41.580
Just to try to figure out how
this would work,

00:00:41.580 --> 00:00:44.374
if you took the birth
narratives of Matthew and Luke

00:00:44.374 --> 00:00:47.126
it would be very,
very difficult to find out

00:00:47.126 --> 00:00:48.910
historically what happened.
 

00:00:48.910 --> 00:00:51.643
For example,
if you just take Matthew,

00:00:51.643 --> 00:00:55.262
as I've said before,
Jesus' family seems to simply

00:00:55.262 --> 00:00:56.740
be in Bethlehem.
 

00:00:56.740 --> 00:00:58.370
It doesn't say they're from
Galilee,

00:00:58.370 --> 00:00:59.980
it doesn't say they're
originally from Nazareth,

00:00:59.980 --> 00:01:02.938
they're just in Bethlehem,
and they're in Bethlehem well

00:01:02.938 --> 00:01:06.165
before Jesus is born because the
wise men in the East see the

00:01:06.165 --> 00:01:09.500
star and it takes them enough
time to travel from Persia,

00:01:09.500 --> 00:01:12.438
we're supposed to understand
from the narrative because

00:01:12.438 --> 00:01:14.807
they're called Magi,
and those are wise men from

00:01:14.807 --> 00:01:17.110
Persia,
all the way to Jerusalem.

00:01:17.110 --> 00:01:19.438
They meet up with King Herod
the Great,

00:01:19.438 --> 00:01:22.388
he gets his wise men to
consult, they then find out

00:01:22.388 --> 00:01:24.688
they're supposed to go to
Bethlehem,

00:01:24.688 --> 00:01:27.677
they journey to Bethlehem,
and then they get there not

00:01:27.677 --> 00:01:29.200
long after Jesus is born.
 

00:01:29.200 --> 00:01:32.194
So according to Matthew,
you don't have any time

00:01:32.194 --> 00:01:35.765
actually in the narrative of
Matthew for the whole moving

00:01:35.765 --> 00:01:39.271
from Nazareth to Bethlehem
narrative that you get in the

00:01:39.271 --> 00:01:40.610
Gospel of Luke.
 

00:01:40.610 --> 00:01:42.430
You just don't have time in
Matthew, they're just there.

00:01:42.430 --> 00:01:46.870
And then the angel appears to
Joseph in a dream and says,

00:01:46.870 --> 00:01:48.730
Herod's going to kill all the
babies,

00:01:48.730 --> 00:01:53.550
so Joseph takes the family,
they move to Egypt for a while.

00:01:53.550 --> 00:01:57.640
He gets another dream years
later, how many years,

00:01:57.640 --> 00:02:00.810
who knows, saying that Herod
the Great is now dead,

00:02:00.810 --> 00:02:04.245
so they go back--they start to
go back to Bethlehem because it

00:02:04.245 --> 00:02:06.049
says that's their home,
right?

00:02:06.049 --> 00:02:07.488
They go back home,
they're going to go to

00:02:07.488 --> 00:02:07.920
Bethlehem.
 

00:02:07.920 --> 00:02:11.471
Instead they move to Galilee to
avoid Herod's son,

00:02:11.471 --> 00:02:14.370
who is at the time,
according to Matthew,

00:02:14.370 --> 00:02:15.819
ruling in Judea.
 

00:02:15.819 --> 00:02:18.310
That's the sort of narrative.
 

00:02:18.310 --> 00:02:20.889
You get to Luke and it's very
different.

00:02:20.889 --> 00:02:24.964
They're from Nazareth,
that's sort of Mary's hometown,

00:02:24.964 --> 00:02:25.810
Nazareth.
 

00:02:25.810 --> 00:02:29.688
All the pregnancy of Mary takes
place with Mary in Nazareth.

00:02:29.688 --> 00:02:33.250
She even goes to Judea to visit
her kinswoman Elizabeth,

00:02:33.250 --> 00:02:36.789
who is the mother of John the
Baptist according to the Gospel

00:02:36.789 --> 00:02:38.419
of Luke,
and then she goes back to

00:02:38.419 --> 00:02:40.167
Nazareth,
and then it's according to this

00:02:40.167 --> 00:02:42.157
census,
the world census that they go

00:02:42.157 --> 00:02:44.390
to Bethlehem,
and it's while they're in

00:02:44.390 --> 00:02:47.236
Bethlehem in the stable,
because you don't have a stable

00:02:47.236 --> 00:02:49.985
in Matthew,
they're just maybe in a home or

00:02:49.985 --> 00:02:53.128
according to a lot of traditions
Jesus was--

00:02:53.128 --> 00:02:56.460
there was a cave somewhere that
Jesus was born in.

00:02:56.460 --> 00:02:59.109
It's in Luke that you get the
whole story about--the Christmas

00:02:59.109 --> 00:03:01.670
story about the stable that
Jesus is born in because there's

00:03:01.670 --> 00:03:02.669
no room in the inn.
 

00:03:02.669 --> 00:03:05.460
They stay in that area for a
month,

00:03:05.460 --> 00:03:07.889
we know that because it says
that they first have Jesus

00:03:07.889 --> 00:03:10.050
circumcised on the eighth day
from his birth,

00:03:10.050 --> 00:03:12.550
and then the time of
purification takes place,

00:03:12.550 --> 00:03:14.628
according to Leviticus,
which is about a month long,

00:03:14.628 --> 00:03:16.127
they take Jesus to the
presentation of the temple in

00:03:16.127 --> 00:03:16.479
Jerusalem.
 

00:03:16.479 --> 00:03:19.316
And it's after that,
so a month or so after his

00:03:19.316 --> 00:03:22.400
birth that they then move back
home to Nazareth.

00:03:22.400 --> 00:03:26.228
Now there's no way you can
basically get these two

00:03:26.228 --> 00:03:31.150
narratives to fit together in
any respectable historical way.

00:03:31.150 --> 00:03:33.160
Does that mean that nobody's
ever tried to do it?

00:03:33.160 --> 00:03:35.020
No, of course you've got all
kinds of very,

00:03:35.020 --> 00:03:38.337
very smart fundamentalists who
believe that the New Testament

00:03:38.337 --> 00:03:41.599
has to be accurate in every
historical and scientific detail

00:03:41.599 --> 00:03:44.199
or they believe then it can't be
scripture.

00:03:44.199 --> 00:03:47.229
They will figure out some way
to try to make sure that both

00:03:47.229 --> 00:03:49.318
these narratives can be fit
together,

00:03:49.318 --> 00:03:52.182
but what I'm telling you is
that no reputable historian will

00:03:52.182 --> 00:03:54.853
accept this because you just
have to fudge the stuff too

00:03:54.853 --> 00:03:56.639
much;
you have to fudge the data.

00:03:56.639 --> 00:03:58.910
What do we believe about the
birth of Jesus?

00:03:58.910 --> 00:04:02.171
Most of us think we don't know
anything about the birth of

00:04:02.171 --> 00:04:02.628
Jesus.
 

00:04:02.628 --> 00:04:05.080
All the Christmas stories are
later tradition,

00:04:05.080 --> 00:04:08.479
probably the one thing most of
us would say is that Jesus

00:04:08.479 --> 00:04:11.598
probably was from Nazareth,
his family was simply from

00:04:11.598 --> 00:04:14.000
Nazareth because he's called
Jesus of Nazareth.

00:04:14.000 --> 00:04:17.560
And the traditions that got him
to Bethlehem for his birth are

00:04:17.560 --> 00:04:20.829
probably later pietistic
traditions that Matthew and Luke

00:04:20.829 --> 00:04:23.339
later developed for different
reasons,

00:04:23.339 --> 00:04:26.958
but to get Jesus born in
Bethlehem for fulfillment of

00:04:26.958 --> 00:04:28.278
prophecy reasons.
 

00:04:28.278 --> 00:04:32.990
If you take the birth of Jesus
in Luke and Matthew,

00:04:32.990 --> 00:04:36.401
it's--from a historical point
of view it's impossible really

00:04:36.401 --> 00:04:39.985
to harmonize them without coming
up with fantastic unbelievable

00:04:39.985 --> 00:04:43.398
conjugations of Jesus moving
back and forth to Egypt and the

00:04:43.398 --> 00:04:46.000
holy family and all this sort of
thing.

00:04:46.000 --> 00:04:50.629
We get lots of other kinds of
things about this too.

00:04:50.629 --> 00:04:53.930
What are some obvious
historical problems with the

00:04:53.930 --> 00:04:55.209
historical Jesus?
 

00:04:55.209 --> 00:04:58.990
Well one of the things is the
trial of Jesus.

00:04:58.990 --> 00:05:02.451
There are different versions of
the trial of Jesus in the

00:05:02.451 --> 00:05:03.069
Gospels.
 

00:05:03.069 --> 00:05:06.692
Unfortunately,
basically most scholars will

00:05:06.692 --> 00:05:11.697
say that we don't really know
what happened at the trial of

00:05:11.697 --> 00:05:12.560
Jesus.
 

00:05:12.560 --> 00:05:15.113
We don't even know for sure
whether there was any kind of

00:05:15.113 --> 00:05:15.889
official trial.
 

00:05:15.889 --> 00:05:18.781
It may have been that he was
just arrested in the middle of

00:05:18.781 --> 00:05:20.843
the night,
he was just then--they give him

00:05:20.843 --> 00:05:23.670
permission to be crucified and
he was crucified the next day.

00:05:23.670 --> 00:05:26.360
That would be the sensible way
of doing things.

00:05:26.360 --> 00:05:29.735
You didn't have to have--the
Romans didn't need elaborate

00:05:29.735 --> 00:05:33.413
trials in order to crucify Jews
who were rabble rousers in the

00:05:33.413 --> 00:05:35.959
first century,
they did it all the time.

00:05:35.959 --> 00:05:38.677
If you look at some of the
details of the trial notice how

00:05:38.677 --> 00:05:39.870
they're very different.
 

00:05:39.870 --> 00:05:43.009
Mark 14, get your Bibles out.
 

00:05:43.009 --> 00:05:46.800
Today we are talking about the
historical Jesus but I'm not

00:05:46.800 --> 00:05:50.788
just going to tell you what I
believe or what scholars believe

00:05:50.788 --> 00:05:54.399
about the historical Jesus,
I'm going to try to show you

00:05:54.399 --> 00:05:56.949
why scholars come up with ideas
that we have,

00:05:56.949 --> 00:05:59.976
how we get there,
what is our method for arriving

00:05:59.976 --> 00:06:02.120
at historical Jesus discussions.
 

00:06:02.120 --> 00:06:05.379
Look at Mark 14:53:
 

00:06:17.028 --> 00:06:19.093
They took Jesus to the high
priest and all the chief

00:06:19.093 --> 00:06:21.278
priests, the elders,
and the scribes were assembled.

00:06:21.278 --> 00:06:23.468
Peter had followed him at a
distance right into the

00:06:23.468 --> 00:06:25.922
courtyard of the high priest,
and he was sitting with the

00:06:25.922 --> 00:06:27.629
guards warming himself at the
fire.

00:06:27.629 --> 00:06:30.026
Now the chief priests and the
whole council were looking for

00:06:30.026 --> 00:06:32.343
testimony against Jesus to put
him to death but they found

00:06:32.343 --> 00:06:32.709
none.
 

00:06:32.709 --> 00:06:35.478
Many gave false testimony
against him and their testimony

00:06:35.478 --> 00:06:36.269
did not agree.
 

00:06:36.269 --> 00:06:38.870
Some stood up and gave false
testimony against him saying,

00:06:38.870 --> 00:06:40.949
"We have heard him say,
'I will destroy this temple

00:06:40.949 --> 00:06:43.410
that is made with hands and in
three days I will build another

00:06:43.410 --> 00:06:45.629
not made with hands.'"
But even on this point their

00:06:45.629 --> 00:06:46.800
testimony did not agree.
 

00:06:46.800 --> 00:06:49.228
Then the high priest stood up
before them and asked Jesus,

00:06:49.228 --> 00:06:50.379
"Have you no answer?
 

00:06:50.379 --> 00:06:52.470
What is it that they testify
against you?"

00:06:52.470 --> 00:06:55.139
But he was silent and did not
answer.

00:06:55.139 --> 00:06:57.377
Again the high priest asked
him, "Are you the Messiah,

00:06:57.377 --> 00:06:58.730
the Son of the Blessed
One?"

00:06:58.730 --> 00:07:00.250
Jesus said, "I am.
 

00:07:00.250 --> 00:07:02.904
And you will see the Son of Man
seated at the right hand of

00:07:02.904 --> 00:07:05.240
power and coming with the clouds
of heaven."

00:07:05.240 --> 00:07:08.269
[That's a quotation from
Daniel, so Jesus basically just

00:07:08.269 --> 00:07:09.911
says,
"I am,"

00:07:09.911 --> 00:07:13.730
and then quotes Daniel.]
The high priest accused him of

00:07:13.730 --> 00:07:14.649
blasphemy.
 

00:07:14.649 --> 00:07:17.815
Then look at chapter 15,
beginning of chapter 15,

00:07:17.815 --> 00:07:19.415
"
As soon as it was morning,

00:07:19.415 --> 00:07:21.583
the chief priests held a
consultation with the elders and

00:07:21.583 --> 00:07:22.860
scribes and the whole council.
 

00:07:22.860 --> 00:07:24.480
They bound Jesus,
led him away,

00:07:24.480 --> 00:07:26.209
and handed him over to Pilate.
 

00:07:26.209 --> 00:07:27.745
Pilate asked him,
"Are you the King of the

00:07:27.745 --> 00:07:28.180
Jews?"
 

00:07:28.180 --> 00:07:29.910
He answered him,
"You say so."

00:07:29.910 --> 00:07:32.040
Then the chief priest accused
him of many things.

00:07:32.040 --> 00:07:33.940
Pilate asked him again,
"Have you no answer?

00:07:33.940 --> 00:07:35.879
See how many charges they bring
against you."

00:07:35.879 --> 00:07:40.389
But Jesus made no further reply
so that Pilate was amazed.

00:07:40.389 --> 00:07:43.930
Now notice all Jesus says at
his trial,

00:07:43.930 --> 00:07:45.997
according to Mark,
the oldest of our written

00:07:45.997 --> 00:07:47.889
testimonies,
is "I am"

00:07:47.889 --> 00:07:50.600
and a quotation of scripture at
one point,

00:07:50.600 --> 00:07:53.827
and then, "so you
say," in the next trial

00:07:53.827 --> 00:07:54.860
before Pilate.
 

00:07:54.860 --> 00:07:58.379
Now compare that to what goes
on in the Gospel of John.

00:07:58.379 --> 00:08:01.668
I mentioned this a bit in my
lecture on the Gospel of John,

00:08:01.668 --> 00:08:05.129
how its narrative details are
very different from the synoptic

00:08:05.129 --> 00:08:05.810
Gospels.
 

00:08:05.810 --> 00:08:08.480
One of the places where this is
really different is the trial of

00:08:08.480 --> 00:08:08.819
Jesus.
 

00:08:08.819 --> 00:08:12.867
John 18:19, I'm not going to
read all of this because it's

00:08:12.867 --> 00:08:15.514
just way too long,
there's a part of--the

00:08:15.514 --> 00:08:18.504
interesting thing is that the
trial of Jesus goes on for a

00:08:18.504 --> 00:08:20.339
long time in the Gospel of John.
 

00:08:20.339 --> 00:08:22.851
The high priest questioned
Jesus about his disciples and

00:08:22.851 --> 00:08:23.810
about his teaching.
 

00:08:23.810 --> 00:08:26.088
Jesus answered,
"I have spoken openly to

00:08:26.088 --> 00:08:26.709
the world.
 

00:08:26.709 --> 00:08:28.932
I have always taught synagogues
near the temple where all the

00:08:28.932 --> 00:08:29.709
Jews come together.
 

00:08:29.709 --> 00:08:30.870
I have said nothing in secret.
 

00:08:30.870 --> 00:08:31.759
Why do you ask me?"
 

00:08:31.759 --> 00:08:35.393
Already Jesus has said a ton
more now than he has said in the

00:08:35.393 --> 00:08:37.149
other Gospels at his trial.
 

00:08:37.149 --> 00:08:41.158
Then he just keeps going on,
he says more things:

00:08:41.158 --> 00:08:43.096
When he had said this,
one of the police standing

00:08:43.096 --> 00:08:44.788
nearby struck Jesus in the face
saying,

00:08:44.788 --> 00:08:46.230
"Is that how you answer
the high priest?"

00:08:46.230 --> 00:08:48.143
Jesus answered,
"If I have spoken wrongly,

00:08:48.143 --> 00:08:49.100
testify to the wrong.
 

00:08:49.100 --> 00:08:50.740
But if I have spoken rightly,
why do you strike me?"

00:08:50.740 --> 00:08:54.168
Then Annas sent him down to
Caiaphas the high priest.

00:08:54.168 --> 00:08:56.964
So according to John,
Annas and Caiaphas are kinfolk,

00:08:56.964 --> 00:08:59.758
and they're sort of both
members of the high priestly

00:08:59.758 --> 00:09:00.350
family.
 

00:09:00.350 --> 00:09:01.750
You can go on and on.
 

00:09:01.750 --> 00:09:09.408
At verse 28 is the trial--they
took Jesus to Pilate.

00:09:09.408 --> 00:09:12.383
Pilate went out to them and
said, "What accusation do

00:09:12.383 --> 00:09:14.210
you bring against this
man?"

00:09:14.210 --> 00:09:15.370
They answered,
"If this man were not a

00:09:15.370 --> 00:09:17.000
criminal, we would not have
handed him over to you."

00:09:17.000 --> 00:09:18.380
Pilate said to them,
"Take him yourselves and

00:09:18.380 --> 00:09:19.509
judge him according to your
law."

00:09:19.509 --> 00:09:20.451
The Jews answered,
"We are not

00:09:20.451 --> 00:09:20.950
permitted."
 

00:09:20.950 --> 00:09:24.230
It goes on, Pilate talks to
Jesus,

00:09:24.230 --> 00:09:25.418
"Are you the King of the
Jews?"

00:09:25.418 --> 00:09:27.081
Jesus answered,
"Do you ask this on your

00:09:27.081 --> 00:09:28.778
own, or did others tell you
about it?"

00:09:28.778 --> 00:09:30.710
Pilate said,
"I am not a Jew,

00:09:30.710 --> 00:09:31.120
am I?
 

00:09:31.120 --> 00:09:33.350
Your own nation and the chief
priests handed you over to me.

00:09:33.350 --> 00:09:34.240
What have you done?"
 

00:09:34.240 --> 00:09:35.320
Jesus said, "My kingdom
is--"

00:09:35.320 --> 00:09:38.313
Jesus just has a whole
conversation with Pilate which

00:09:38.313 --> 00:09:41.480
leads to that wonderfully
quotable phrase that everybody

00:09:41.480 --> 00:09:44.879
knows about where finally Jesus
talks about truth and Pilate

00:09:44.879 --> 00:09:48.104
says in a phrase that could be
sincere or a lot of people

00:09:48.104 --> 00:09:51.230
answered as being cynical,
"What is truth?"

00:09:51.230 --> 00:09:54.308
Very famous quotation from the
Gospel of John.

00:09:54.308 --> 00:09:57.211
Then of course there's the
whole passage,

00:09:57.211 --> 00:09:59.969
any of you seen
the--"Jesus Christ

00:09:59.969 --> 00:10:03.090
Superstar,"
the play or the movie?

