00:24:06.769 --> 00:24:08.907
If you could faster,
than the speed of light,

00:24:08.907 --> 00:24:11.824
fly out to that thing you could
actually experience the Civil

00:24:11.824 --> 00:24:13.380
War as it actually happened.
 

00:24:13.380 --> 00:24:17.893
Well maybe theoretically,
but for any of us sitting here

00:24:17.893 --> 00:24:21.338
in this room,
that's not possible is it?

00:24:21.338 --> 00:24:25.656
In other words,
this is a radical thought to

00:24:25.656 --> 00:24:31.380
some people, but the past no
longer exists for you and me,

00:24:31.380 --> 00:24:33.788
it's radically gone.
 

00:24:33.788 --> 00:24:40.398
The past is non-existent when
it comes to our experiences of

00:24:40.398 --> 00:24:40.960
it.
 

00:24:40.960 --> 00:24:44.750
All we can experience are
different accounts of the past.

00:24:44.750 --> 00:24:47.710
We can experience different
constructions of the past.

00:24:47.710 --> 00:24:50.609
We cannot experience the past
itself.

00:24:50.609 --> 00:24:54.298
It's gone;
it's lost to us forever.

00:24:54.298 --> 00:24:59.430
That means the historical
Jesus, as Jesus actually existed

00:24:59.430 --> 00:25:02.759
