00:30:31.440 --> 00:30:36.369
One of the things that most
scholars will say is,

00:30:36.369 --> 00:30:39.349
we think that's historical.
 

00:30:39.349 --> 00:30:41.740
Why do we think it's historical?
 

00:30:41.740 --> 00:30:45.015
Well, for one thing,
it comes from at least two

00:30:45.015 --> 00:30:47.078
independent sources,
right?

00:30:47.078 --> 00:30:49.818
What are the two independent
sources that it comes from?

00:30:49.818 --> 00:30:52.849
It's in all four Gospels but
all four Gospels aren't

00:30:52.849 --> 00:30:54.574
independent sources are they?
 

00:30:54.574 --> 00:30:54.990
Why?
 

00:30:54.990 --> 00:30:58.106
Because we believe that Matthew
and Luke used Mark,

00:30:58.106 --> 00:31:00.726
so if Matthew and Luke copied
it from Mark,

00:31:00.726 --> 00:31:02.660
that makes Mark one source.
 

00:31:02.660 --> 00:31:05.660
Did the author of John use the
Gospel of Mark?

00:31:05.660 --> 00:31:08.288
Not according to the theory
we're using in this class.

00:31:08.288 --> 00:31:10.588
Some people might say yes,
some scholars might say yes,

00:31:10.588 --> 00:31:13.380
but in this class we're going
on the theory that the Gospel of

00:31:13.380 --> 00:31:15.848
John probably didn't use Mark as
one of his sources.

00:31:15.848 --> 00:31:18.308
You've got the Gospel of John
as one source for this;

00:31:18.308 --> 00:31:20.940
you've got the Gospel of Mark
as another source for this,

00:31:20.940 --> 00:31:23.344
so you have two of what
scholars are willing to treat as

00:31:23.344 --> 00:31:25.766
independent sources,
which both have this nice

00:31:25.766 --> 00:31:29.068
little piece of data,
this data right there.

00:31:29.068 --> 00:31:31.280
Now the other thing is
that--might be interesting for

00:31:31.280 --> 00:31:34.182
you to know,
"King of the Jews"

00:31:34.182 --> 00:31:39.112
is not a Christological title
that early Christians used about

00:31:39.112 --> 00:31:39.838
Jesus.
 

00:31:39.838 --> 00:31:43.853
Remember in the Gospels we've
seen a lot of different titles

00:31:43.853 --> 00:31:44.670
for Jesus.
 

00:31:44.670 --> 00:31:47.011
He's the teacher,
he's the Son of God,

00:31:47.011 --> 00:31:49.987
he's the Messiah,
he's the Holy one of Israel we

00:31:49.987 --> 00:31:50.808
just saw.
 

00:31:50.808 --> 00:31:53.820
He was a lot of things,
and these things are obviously

00:31:53.820 --> 00:31:55.909
things--
early Christians call him Lord,

00:31:55.909 --> 00:31:59.643
they called him Son of God,
but they didn't call him King

00:31:59.643 --> 00:32:00.680
of the Jews.
 

00:32:00.680 --> 00:32:04.325
It was one of the titles of
Jesus that apparently the

00:32:04.325 --> 00:32:07.690
earliest followers of Jesus
didn't latch onto.

00:32:07.690 --> 00:32:10.807
So we don't see it in the
letters of Paul and we don't see

00:32:10.807 --> 00:32:12.450
it elsewhere in the Gospels.
 

00:32:12.450 --> 00:32:14.598
So what scholars have said is,
look,

00:32:14.598 --> 00:32:17.547
this thing King of the Jews
doesn't look like a

00:32:17.547 --> 00:32:21.134
Christological confessional
title that Christians made up

00:32:21.134 --> 00:32:23.250
and then put into the Gospel.
 

00:32:23.250 --> 00:32:28.492
It goes against the tendency of
the Christian writers themselves

00:32:28.492 --> 00:32:31.740
because it's not one of their
titles.

00:32:31.740 --> 00:32:33.537
If it had said,
"This is Jesus of

00:32:33.537 --> 00:32:35.377
Nazareth,
the Lord of heaven and

00:32:35.377 --> 00:32:37.608
earth," then scholars would
say,

00:32:37.608 --> 00:32:39.180
well that sounds like a
Christian confession.

00:32:39.180 --> 00:32:41.585
But saying, "Jesus of
Nazareth, King of the

00:32:41.585 --> 00:32:44.808
Jews," doesn't sound like a
Christian confession so it goes

00:32:44.808 --> 00:32:47.727
against the tendency of the
writers themselves and then we

00:32:47.727 --> 00:32:49.172
say,
well maybe then it's

00:32:49.172 --> 00:32:51.817
historical, maybe it's a little
glimpse of history sitting in

00:32:51.817 --> 00:32:53.500
there,
so that's one thing.

00:32:53.500 --> 00:32:56.977
The sign on the cross,
most scholars say that's

00:32:56.977 --> 00:32:57.960
historical.
 

