00:33:33.910 --> 00:33:38.026
One other thing that scholars
often say may well be

00:33:38.026 --> 00:33:42.390
historical: Jesus was baptized
by John the Baptist.

00:33:42.390 --> 00:33:45.568
Why would scholars say this is
historical?

00:33:45.568 --> 00:33:49.750
Well there's not complete
agreement about how it happened.

00:33:49.750 --> 00:33:53.492
The Gospel of John doesn't
exactly tell you about the

00:33:53.492 --> 00:33:58.029
baptism of Jesus by John but it
has Jesus and his disciples,

00:33:58.029 --> 00:34:00.558
also baptized in the Jordan,
and it has Jesus very much

00:34:00.558 --> 00:34:03.509
connected to John the Baptist in
the beginning of its Gospel.

00:34:03.509 --> 00:34:06.976
The other Gospels do have Jesus
baptized by John,

00:34:06.976 --> 00:34:09.719
but notice how the story goes
along.

00:34:09.719 --> 00:34:14.846
All of the writers who have
Jesus baptized by John the

00:34:14.846 --> 00:34:17.367
Baptist,
they have Jesus come to John

00:34:17.367 --> 00:34:19.920
the Baptist and they say I want
to be baptized,

00:34:19.920 --> 00:34:23.230
and John the Baptist says,
oh no I shouldn't baptize you,

00:34:23.230 --> 00:34:27.820
you're the big kahuna,
you're bigger then I am.

00:34:27.820 --> 00:34:31.099
I'm not worthy to untie your
sandals,

00:34:31.099 --> 00:34:33.190
so I should be baptized by you,
you shouldn't--

00:34:33.190 --> 00:34:35.530
I shouldn't be baptizing you
and Jesus says,

00:34:35.530 --> 00:34:38.150
no, no, no, it's okay baptize
me and so he does it and then

00:34:38.150 --> 00:34:40.952
you have the confession and the
voice from heaven and that sort

00:34:40.952 --> 00:34:41.539
of thing.
 

00:34:41.539 --> 00:34:43.909
Notice what's going on here.
 

00:34:43.909 --> 00:34:48.217
The Gospel writers are very
concerned because they know that

00:34:48.217 --> 00:34:52.527
it could be interpreted that
John baptizing Jesus makes John

00:34:52.527 --> 00:34:56.690
superior to Jesus and makes
Jesus a disciple of John.

00:34:56.690 --> 00:34:59.643
And they're not comfortable
with that because of course they

00:34:59.643 --> 00:35:02.597
believed Jesus is the Messiah
and so he's therefore superior

00:35:02.597 --> 00:35:05.655
to John the Baptist,
and John the Baptist was just a

00:35:05.655 --> 00:35:07.579
prophet or a precursor to Jesus.
 

00:35:07.579 --> 00:35:12.465
The story is told to play down
this baptism a bit and make

00:35:12.465 --> 00:35:16.409
Jesus come out as insisting on
the baptism,

00:35:16.409 --> 00:35:20.472
wanting to do it for the right
kinds of reasons but not making

00:35:20.472 --> 00:35:22.268
Jesus a disciple of John.
 

00:35:22.268 --> 00:35:25.918
And also this tradition about
the baptism of Jesus is in

00:35:25.918 --> 00:35:28.440
different sources in different
ways.

00:35:28.440 --> 00:35:32.005
Again, scholars say,
the baptism of John the Baptist

00:35:32.005 --> 00:35:36.130
baptizing Jesus doesn't look
like something early Christians

00:35:36.130 --> 00:35:37.389
would make up.
 

00:35:37.389 --> 00:35:40.509
In fact, you can even see that
they try to tone down its

00:35:40.509 --> 00:35:41.360
implications.
 

00:35:41.360 --> 00:35:43.570
It's not something they're
likely to make up,

00:35:43.570 --> 00:35:47.380
it kind of goes against their
tradition of raising Jesus up

00:35:47.380 --> 00:35:49.333
completely,
and therefore,

00:35:49.333 --> 00:35:50.960
it may be historical.
 

00:35:50.960 --> 00:35:52.210
Notice what we've got then.
 

00:35:52.210 --> 00:35:55.349
We've got two very small
details that a lot of scholars

00:35:55.349 --> 00:35:58.373
would say probably are
historical because they seemed

00:35:58.373 --> 00:36:02.036
to be witnessed by more than one
source and they also seem to go

00:36:02.036 --> 00:36:05.349
against the theological tendency
of the documents in which

00:36:05.349 --> 00:36:06.630
they're found.
 

00:36:06.630 --> 00:36:09.130
And they frame the Gospel of
Jesus.

00:36:09.130 --> 00:36:12.784
The baptism of Jesus,
the beginning of his ministry,

00:36:12.784 --> 00:36:16.655
and the charge on the cross at
the end of his ministry,

00:36:16.655 --> 00:36:19.018
and now I'm going to back up.
 

00:36:19.018 --> 00:36:21.514
Those two events,
let's just say I'm going to

00:36:21.514 --> 00:36:25.146
